Michael Nyqvist, the Swedish actor who appeared in the original &ldquo;Girl with the Dragon Tattoo&rdquo; films as well as &ldquo;John Wick,&rdquo; has died. He was 56.&nbsp;A representative for the actor confirmed the news to HuffPost Tuesday with the following statement: &nbsp;On behalf of Michael Nyqvist&rsquo;s representatives and family, it is with deep sadness that I can confirm that our beloved Michael, one of Sweden&rsquo;s most respected and accomplished actors, has passed away quietly surrounded by family after a year long battle with lung cancer.&nbsp;&ldquo;Michael&rsquo;s joy and passion were infectious to those who knew and loved him,&rdquo; his family said in a statement to The Associated Press. &ldquo;His charm and charisma were undeniable, and his love for the arts was felt by all who had the pleasure of working with him.&rdquo;Throughout his career, Nyqvist starred in a number of different roles, perhaps most notably as Mikael Blomkvist in the Swedish film adaptations of Stieg Larsson&rsquo;s &ldquo;The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo&rdquo; trilogy. The actor reprised that role in &ldquo;Millennium,&rdquo; a six-part Swedish TV series that expanded on the initial trilogy.&nbsp;His first major role was in the 2000 film &ldquo;Together,&rdquo; which earned Nyqvist his first Best Actor nomination at the Guldbagge Awards, which recognizes achievements in the Swedish film industry.&nbsp;Nyqvist has also appeared in a number of films in the United States, including, &ldquo;John Wick,&rdquo; &ldquo;Mission Impossible: Ghost Protocol&rdquo; and &ldquo;Frank and Lola.&rdquo; He also has a number of films in post-production, including &ldquo;Radegund&rdquo; and &ldquo;Hunter Killer.&rdquo;Share this slide: